# Actual-Diff and Local Verification (`checkpoint:impl-verified`)

Treat reports of intent as unverified until the repository proves the result.
This rule is the evidence half of [gate-dag.md](../references/gate-dag.md)
`checkpoint:impl-verified`.

- Inspect `git status` and the actual `git diff` before reporting implementation complete. Include untracked files (`git add -N` when needed so they appear in the diff).
- Read and spot-check the files claimed to have changed. If the diff is absent or differs from the report, state the discrepancy and do not claim completion.
- Run `checkpoint:impl-verified` before any gate agent:
  - In this harness repository, on any non-docs-only diff: `npm run validate`.
  - Plus task-specific verification from the brief (tests, build, lint, stack floors).
- Confirm the checks exercise the requested golden path and material edge cases.
- Report commands and outcomes accurately; do not turn skipped or unavailable checks into passes. Skipped checks block `checkpoint:ship-ready` unless the human explicitly waives.
- After local verification succeeds, **record the verify ledger** before `gh pr create` or `gh pr ready`:
  - `npm run verify:record -- --run -- <cmd>` (or `--cmd '…' --exit N`) so `.cursor/verify-ledger.json` proves `impl_verified` for the current HEAD.
  - The shell guard denies `gh pr create|ready` unless that ledger is valid (`gh-pr-without-verify`). Emergency only: `VERIFY_PR_GATE_DISABLED=1` skips this check.
- Do not declare work complete, open or ready a PR, merge, tag, or release until [gate-dag.md](../references/gate-dag.md) `checkpoint:ship-ready` clears.
